# Commit and Release Hygiene

- Keep commits focused to one concern; avoid mixing unrelated refactors.
- Review for security, performance, and backward compatibility before completion.
- Remove dead code, debug snippets, and temporary scaffolding before commit.
- Confirm new strings are translation-ready and text domain usage is consistent.
- Document behavior changes affecting templates, hooks, or public APIs.
- Avoid shipping breaking changes without explicit approval and migration notes.
- Verify dependency additions are necessary, maintained, and minimal.
